# Home NAS Lab â€“ Project Summary

## Overview
This project documents the design and operation of a personal NAS environment,
created as a learning-focused home lab to gain hands-on experience in system administration.

## Objectives
- Centralized file storage
- Data protection through backups
- User and permission management
- Understanding storage and infrastructure fundamentals

## Technical Scope
- NAS operating system: OpenMediaVault / Synology DSM
- RAID-based storage configuration
- User and group-based access control
- Scheduled backups
- Basic monitoring and troubleshooting

## Key Learnings
- Storage planning and redundancy concepts
- Practical permission management
- Importance of documentation in system operations
- Systematic approach to troubleshooting

